I was a bit busy turning thirty when Tetzschner spread falsehoods about the Disability Human Rights Convention (CRPD) on # dax18, but here's a thread about how wrong he is. ungefunk ffotweet handicap association nim_norge 1 /

The UN committee cannot sanction Norway for violations, but can make criticisms and recommendations. one would think that a lawyer like tetzschner knew the difference between international and supranational bodies. it may be embarrassing with name and shame and forefinger, but that's all.

the committee can be said to be progressive, but the women's committee and the children's committee have also had a reputation for it at times. none of the committees consists of only lawyers. Disabled people's organizations have long asked Norway to propose a committee member - including lawyers - but Norway has refused.
moreover, norway voted for the committee composition when the convention text was adopted at un.

tetszchner believes that the crpd conflicts with the "real" human rights, but tell me: does not the right think that the conventions for children, women and racial discrimination are real human rights?

the truth is that disabled people have less legal security in norway. we are thought of as patients and users, we are housed together in "housing associations", we receive poorer education, do not get a job, do not have access to a number of buildings, goods, services or information.

this is a question of equality, not health rights. there is a need for systematic change. it is about actually fulfilling the right to education, work, independence, housing, health, information, freedom of movement, freedom of association, freedom of expression.
tetzschner believes that the Guardianship Act is a good example of Norwegian legislation being good. well, i think some brothers in tolga disagree.

The committee has stated that disability in itself should not justify coercion against individuals. it must be linked to illness, situation or need for protection. the practice of the Guardianship Act threatens the legal security of those placed under guardianship.

so yes, we want to change some of the legislation. yes, we will strengthen our rule of law. we want freedom and authority over our own lives. we are shitty nice talk about a warmer society, and inclusion charity, and equality. give us equality and freedom.

based on ssbs 2019 figures for housing conditions, 76,603 lived in detached houses in oslo. in western Norway, 359,544 lived in detached houses. in oslo, 438,906 lived in block of flats, while in the west, 116,494 lived in blocks of flats.

ssb registered that 136,826 people in oslo lived cramped, while 64,393 had the same status in western Norway. the definition of cramped living space: "1) the number of rooms in the dwelling is less than the number of persons ... and 2) the number of square meters is less than 25 m ^ 2 per person."

vestland thus constitutes 9/10 of oslo in population. remember now that the national strategy allocates vaccines according to population so in other words oslo and vestland get proportionally equal parts. further details are not shared with the public by the government, according to what I find.

then to the infection situation. the number tested per county is not reported, but the number of reported positives is resp. 19,405 and 6,774. oslo “leader” with almost 3 times. the statistics on the number of respirators are thin, but in oslo there are 23 people while in the west there are 6, also 3x, per week 7.

If you want to look at the number admitted to the intensive care unit, then these statistics are not broken down by county, but health south-east reports a total of 359 admitted to the intensive care unit, while health west reports 66. this is too poor reporting of a particularly important parameter.

in oslo, 36,610 have now been vaccinated with the first dose, and in the west, the same number is 36,621 per fhis report for week 7. the counties are thus approximately equal in the number of first-time vaccinated.

this is a "new" type of deception. sure, funny pun too, but; a page on facebook holds a contest. The prizes are often nice, hefty or fun and a large number of participants write their answer in the comments field.

suddenly you who have written a reply get a message from what apparently looks like that company or whatever it is. you have won! you see that the sender is the same name as the page you commented in the comment field to, and the image is the same.
and the message says you have to hurry. often you get a deadline. and a link. there you are often asked to provide account details or other personal items. but often it's just a hoax.

How can you be safer in dealing with such? is the sender of the message a page, or a person? If there is a page you should go to the page where you originally left is the answer to the competition, and then check the page that sends you the message. most likely there are differences you will notice.

check the page that sent you the message. when was it created, it has posts from far back etc. is there a person who is "named" the same as since you left a comment on, this is something that should make the alarm bells ring.
Having to provide account details is strange enough in itself, but why do you reach it to get a prize?

are you unsure? do not click on any links. contact the page where you left a comment and ask if they sent you a message. read the comment field if necessary. others have most likely experienced the same thing and have commented on it.
